column4:
I haven't seen you around here before,
are you lost?
Just keep moving to the right,
I'm sure it will all work out
just fine.

Sorry for being in Bilocation
But I had to tell you,
Watch out for the bombs,
They are pretty hostile,
I wouldn't want my new friend
getting hurt.

Wow, I'm surprised you got past
Your first enemy,
Maybe I should have some more hope in you,
Perhaps I should ask you for some help
…

Hey there!
Why don't you try using WASD
to get yourself moving around
You can always double jump,
Use R to restart
And skip signs by pressing E
Talk to characters by holding E

Some coins may be harder to get
than others,
but by collecting all the coins on a level
you will be rewarded!

You haven't seen any of my
friends around have you?
It's just, I'm not sure where the last place
I saw Larry was, he said he would meet
me here…

I don't understand
where Larry could have gotten to.
This is his house
Why isn’t he here like we arranged.

I bet you think I have
No friends now, I swear I do,
They all seem to have gone missing.
Thanks for sticking around to help me
look for them all.

Something seriously
Bad is going on.
I'm sure Larry and Gary would love
to meet you,
this isn't like
them at all...
I've Found Larry!\nI can't fit down to rescue him,\nCan you help me?

I can't reach that block over there,
Larry said If I got it,
I could fit down to rescue him,
But my legs are too short to get there,
Darn my lilliputian limbs.

Thank you so much for saving me!
My name's Larry,
I'll be sure to remember you for this,
I don't even know how I got down here…
Gary is stuck just like I was.\nCan you save him?

I don't want to talk about
how I even got here.
It's about time someone
saved me,
trust Tim to get someone else
to do all the work for him…

Tim told me you'd like the chance
 to win some coins,
 go to the portal and I'll test your
reaction times against mine.
Next time you see me,
a press 'e' when the green changes
to red,
if you're faster than me
you win!

I can't say I'm happy,
but that's quite an impressive speed,
here are your coins as promised
since you beat my time.

Unlucky, well I say unlucky,
but there isn't any luck involved
I'm not a charity worker
but I feel bad for you
for losing to me,
here is 30 coins.
I'm thinking of taking a trip to,\nsomewhere nice and warm,\nit's getting pretty close to winter here.
I couldn't agree more with you Tim,\nI'll come too!
Is nobody going to invite our friend?\nI'm sure Larry wouldn't mind.

After talking to Lary,
we've all decided to invite you
on the little holiday we are having.
We've booked you a place
on the next plane.
I bet your glad I persuaded him,\nor this would be a very short game…

Man, I totally forgot about you,
where have you been?
It's been weeks since we came to the desert,
you must have gotten  lost.
The other two
have already flew off to the jungle,
for their next holiday.
I didn't want to set off without finding
you first,they gave up looking for
you a while ago.

My flights about to leave,
guess this is goodbye,
we had a nice adventure together atleast,
shame the others aren’t here
to say goodbye.
Oh yeah there's this trampoline here
if you are into that kinda thing.
Cya later.
Thanks very much for playing,\nyou'll find some lovely information on,\nthe signs in this final level.

The source code for this game
Is 2,315 lines long,
which makes 9,333 words
and 116,402 characters.
This game was started\non 29th June 2016\nFinishing on 7th June 2017.
The game uses 161 famous\nquotes for the loading\nscreens for all the levels.

I've ran out of facts,
but thanks again
for playing.



~Jonathan Alderson
